for(initialization; condition; increment/decrement) {
 // statements
}
Example: for(i=0; i<10; i++) { }

while(condition) {
 // statements
}
Condition is checked before execution; loop continues while condition is true.

do {
 // statements
} while(condition);
Executes at least once, then checks condition. Useful for menu-driven embedded applications.

void delay(unsigned int count) {
 unsigned int i, j;
 for(i=0; i<count; i++)
 for(j=0; j<127; j++);
}
